## PRISM Coding Rules

1. Always use TypeScript. Prefer React Server Components by default, and only use Client Components when interactivity or browser APIs require it.
2. Keep reusable UI primitives in `components/ui`.
3. Keep feature-specific components in `features/<feature>`.
4. Prefer composable, small components over monolithic components.
5. Respect the established dark/matte Tailwind design system (`micro-*` palette and related tokens/utilities).
6. Do not add new libraries without asking first. If a dependency may be needed, propose 2-3 options with trade-offs before implementation.
